             <animate attributename="offset" dur="2s" repeatcount="indefinite" values="-2; 2">
             </animate>
            </stop>
            <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#f0f0f0" stop-opacity="1">
             <animate attributename="offset" dur="2s" repeatcount="indefinite" values="-1; 3">
             </animate>
            </stop>
           </lineargradient>
          </defs>
         </svg>
        </div>
       </div>

                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   I'm going to be completely honest, I eat at Garrafa's at least once a week. But let me tell you why. I am a hardcore Mexican and Im very picky when it comes to Birria. I grew up eating home mad birria with my abuelitas recipe from mexico. I have never liked eating birria tacos at any restaurant in the US until I tried Garrafa's. I started off with one taco just to see what the hype was about and ended up eating four that day. So believe me when I say "I'm hooked".
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Today I had an itch to try their adobada tacos. I was completely satisfied with my decision.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   The cooks are super down to earth and give you the authentic Mexican street taco vibes. They are quick when it comes to preparing your food and their service is amazing.
                  </span>
                 </p>
                </div>

                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   A coworker and I recently visit this hidden gem and I must say I'm sure glad we food this yummy place. We tried the Tostilokos which were great, nice and spicy, their Quesobirra tacos de Cameron and de res which was served with lots of shrimp, meat and lots of cheese, a nice spicy habanero salad and all their salsa. Portioned really well and greatly served. They don't hold back. We also tried the RuSangria drink and that was really good! Definitely worth a try. The ladies making everything are so kind and welcoming.  Great customer service! We'll definitely be going back to try something different.

                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   7/10/20
                   <br/>
                   Came here from a recommendation from a friend. I ordered the tejuin which I wouldn't recommend unless you're into trying completely new and different things. This is a drink that's mixed with masa flour and taste just like a corn tortilla. Not my favorite but now I know what it tastes like. I also, ordered a fruit cup with the traditional fresh squeezed lime juice, chamoy, valentyna hot sauce and tajune seasoning. It was so delicious and fresh! They were kind and cut up my fruit smaller to make it convenient to eat during my drives. Would definitely come back here again!
                  </span>
